+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GFPz4zUMLJYB5tbfUr5GD6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Reframes from the Pivot:**\n\n1. **Don't build 12 features — build 1 state machine and 12 transition rules.** The Task class has states: `waiting`, `pending`, `active`, `completed`, `failed`. Every \"feature\" is a condition on when/how transitions happen.\n\n2. **Priority, delay, dependencies are all \"readiness guards\"** — conditions that must be true before a task can transition from `waiting`/`pending` to `active`. They compose naturally.\n\n3. **Retry is a `failed → pending` transition with a counter guard.** Dead letter is what happens when the counter guard rejects.\n\n4. **Concurrency is a semaphore on the `pending → active` transition.** \n\n5. **Middleware is an interceptor chain on transitions.**\n\n6. **Graceful shutdown is: stop accepting new tasks, drain active tasks, close.**\n\nThis means the architecture should be: `TaskQueue` (manages queues) → `Queue` (one named queue) → `Task` (state machine). The Queue's `process()` loop is the transition engine."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":150,"cache_read_input_tokens":19974,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":150},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f27f16f-0c55-4db4-b21c-91af69c44b8f","uuid":"8c759b6c-2b36-4975-b99d-60558f531920"}
